Code PLINF and PLINQ

) The Employee Plan/Exempt Organization Application Control System is a system to control the various application forms for Employee Plans and Exempt Organizations. The Plan Case Control File (PCCF) contains the complete information required to control the applications: plan entity information such as name and address, controlling information such status and specialist assignment, and ﬁnal disposition of the application. PCCF is accessed via a special case number, which is computer with the initial creation of each case on EDS (EP/EO Determination the KDO (Key District Office). This is a unique number based on the Office of input and the current julian date. The case number used to be created by Command Code PLADD which became obsolete on
was replaced by the EDS system on
) Purpose: This transmits revised IRM
, IDRS Terminal Responses, Command Code PLINF and PLINQ. (
) Audience: LMSB, SB/SE, TE/GE, W&I (
) Program Owner: Customer Service (
) Primary Stakeholders: Wage & Investment (W & I), Large Business and national (LB & I), Small Business Self-Employed (SB/SE), Tax Exempt and Government Entities (TE/GE). (
) Program Goals: Search for case numbers when only key data is known. Display information currently on the PCCF for a particular case. (

) The case number is in the format DOYJJJnnnaa. DO is the input DO is the current list year digit, JJJ is the input julian date, nnn is the Format serial number, and aa is the identifying alpha two character ﬁle source. a. EP - District Office Employee Plan Case b. EO - District Office Exempt Organization Case (

) In addition to the Plan Case Control File (PCCF), abbreviated information each case is maintained on the Plan/Organization Index File (POIF). The Index is used to retrieve the case number when only limited data such as the Number, EIN, Employer/Sponsor or Organization Name Control and, on cases, the Plan Number is available. (
) The POIF may be interrogated by any single key element (except the Plan Number) or any combination of key data elements. Other data elements be input when the Plan Number is an input element. (

) The information displayed by CC PLINF varies according to the input command code deﬁner and the input ﬁle source. PLINF a. There is a ﬁxed data section for ﬁle source EP and another ﬁxed section for ﬁle source EO. The ﬁxed data section is displayed on one of the output display when command code deﬁner of b (blank) is used. Management Report History, Transaction History and Status Assignment History sections, which provide complete history and ling information, are also displayed when deﬁner b (blank) is used.
Program Goals: Search for case numbers when only key data is known. Display information currently on the PCCF for a particular case.
The information displayed by CC PLINF varies according to the input command code deﬁner and the input ﬁle source.

There is a ﬁxed data section for ﬁle source EP and another ﬁxed data section for ﬁle source EO. The ﬁxed data section is displayed on page one of the output display when command code deﬁner of b (blank) is used. Management Report History, Transaction History and Status and Assignment History sections, which provide complete history and ling information, are also displayed when deﬁner b (blank) is used.

for multiple outputs. Certain identifying data is redisplayed on second and all quent pages. b. When command code deﬁner “E” is used, complete name and address information is displayed. The ﬁxed data section will not be displayed. (

) CC PLINQ is used to ﬁnd a case number(s) when only key data is known. PLINQ has two deﬁners: “b” (blank) and “ O”. When command code deﬁner b (blank) is used, only cases with ﬁle sources EP are shown. Exempt tion cases (ﬁle source EO) are displayed by input of CC PLINQ with code deﬁner “O” (alpha).
When command code deﬁner “E” is used, complete name and address information is displayed. The ﬁxed data section will not be displayed.

CC DEFINER INVALID - Input CC Deﬁner is other than “b” (blank) or “
”. Correct and reenter.
CORRECT INVALID DATA ON SCREEN - One or more key data elements is incorrect. element(s) will be marked with an asterisk. Correct and reenter.
NO DATA AVAILABLE - No matching records are present on the POIF, even after all possible defaulting.
SEARCH KEY INCOMPLETE - No key data element (File Folder Number, EIN, Name Control) was input. Input at least one key data element reenter.
BMF ACCESS RESTRICTED - Employee proﬁle will not allow BMF Access.

POIF will be searched for one or more records matching the key data elements. If no records matching the data elements as input are found, key data elements will be dropped until one or more matches is found or no key data elements are left. If key data elements are dropped, the message “SEARCH KEY DEFAULT” be displayed.
Valid Response when more than one matching POIF record is found.
